headline.main: THE HOUSE-PAINTERS' STRIKE.; Probable Termination of the Difficulties. DISPENSARY REPORTS FOR AUGUST. THE HEALTH OF REV. DR. PHILLIPS.
Yellow Fever at New-Orleans--The Mortailry or three Months.
Latest from New-Orleans, Charleston and Savannah.

docs.lead_paragraph: By the arrival of the Crescent City we have received the New-Orleans Picayune to the 25th ult. As we have already gathered from our telegraphic dispatches, the deaths from yellow fever were on the decrease. The Board of Health had advertised for eleven physicians, at a salary of $200 per month.

headline.main: GREAT BRITAIN.; The Royal Vielt to Ireland--Parliamentary Hon. Mrs. Nortoin--Miscellaneuos Intelligence.

docs.lead_paragraph: The royal visit to Ireland will be far more private than accords with the tastes and interests of the Dublin folks. Neither levee nor drawing-room will be held during the stay of her Majesty; and even the visit to the Exhibition is to be managed as quietly as possible.

headline.main: TEMPERANCE.; Whole World's Temperance Convention. SECOND DAY.

docs.lead_paragraph: This Assembly resumed its sittings yesterday morning. A large number of both ladies and gentlemen were present in the lobby of the Hall. The Chairman having read the resolutions brought forward at the previous day's meeting, the Amphions sang a Temperance hymn, beginning with the words, ' Intemperance, like a raging flood."

headline.main: Medical.; A PRETTY ROW. Court of Impeachment for the Trial of John C. Mather, Canal Commissioner.

docs.lead_paragraph: A PRETTY ROW.--The politicians have not all the fun. The doctors come in for a share. Witness the following: The Commercial Hospital and Lunatic Asylum at Cincinnati is, it seems, under the control of the Medical College of Ohio, and the physicians who have no inside chance, have came to the conclusion that there is something wrong about it.

headline.main: WOMAN AND TEMPERANCE.; Great Female Demonstration. Convention at Metropolitan Hall. EVENING SESSION.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Whole World's Temperance Convention assembled at Metropolitan Hall, at 10 o'clock yesterday morning. The house was fairly occupied--not to make a pun. There were probably a thousand persons present, and they were very attentive. The parquette was nearly all occupied, and the first circle received a thin sprinkling.
